The paper deals with the decidability of infinite games with imperfect information, which is a topic in logic (cs.LO) and game theory (cs.GT). The focus is on synchronous games with perfect recall, which are often studied in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and distributed systems (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the concept of information hierarchy, which is relevant to control and coordination in multi-agent systems (cs.SY).
